GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The Form 990 is reviewed by the Senior Accountant, CFO, and CEO of the organization. After satisfactory review, it is presented to the Finance Committee for review.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The organization requires that all employees and Board members disclose in writing and update at least annually, all business and immediate family relationships which might potentially create a conflict of interest. In additions, employees must disclose to the President/CEO, and President/CEO must disclose to the Board Chairperson, in writing the specifics of any plan to accept outside employment so that outside employment may be determined if potential conflict exists.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15a
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The Board of directors interviews, hires, and negotiates the salary of the CEO.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Form 990 is made available upon request.
